==Old Armenian==

===Etymology===
From {{bor|xcl|ira-mid}} {{m|und||*-ak}}, from {{der|xcl|ira-pro|*-akah}}. Compare also {{cog|oge|-აკი}}.

According to Asatrian, the agent-noun-forming suffix is etymologically distinct and is borrowed from {{bor|xcl|ira-mid}} {{m|und||*-āk}}. According to him, it is found in the following wholly borrowed terms: {{m|xcl|դերձակ}}, {{m|xcl|վարձակ}}, {{m|xcl|պատմուճակ}}, {{m|xcl|նուիրակ}} and perhaps {{m|xcl|աւազակ}}.

===Suffix===
{{head|xcl|suffix}}{{cln|xcl|diminutive suffixes}}

# {{non-gloss|forming diminutives from nominal stems}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[աթոռ]]|t=chair|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[աթոռակ]]|t=small chair|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[նաւ]]|t=ship|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[նաւակ]]|t=boat|inline=1}}
# {{non-gloss|forming [[agent noun]]s from verbal stems}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[գտանեմ]]|t=to find, invent|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[գտակ]]|t=inventor|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[լողամ]]|t=to swim|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[լողակ]]|t=swimmer|inline=1}}
# {{non-gloss|forming adjectives}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[բոլորակ]]|t=circular|inline=1}}
# {{non-gloss|forming nouns from verbs}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[է]]|t=is|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[էակ]]|t=being|inline=1}}
# {{non-gloss|forming nouns from adjectives, adverbs and pronouns}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[քանի]]|t=how many?|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|xcl|[[քանակ]]|t=quantity|inline=1}}

